<br>
/attack<br>
/say &quot;You will squirm in fear little worm!&quot; or &quot;Die you gravy sucking pig!&quot; or &quot;In the name of Brell, %T must die!&quot; or &quot;All right, who ordered %T onna stick?&quot;<br>
/doability 1<br>
/loc<br>
<br>
This has the advantage of giving you a loc as you start your fight, and you may forget to do one later. Also, if you use one of the latter two /says or a variant thereof, folks know if you have the right mob targeted and can tell you if you don't notice. And yes, I do this too much. That's why I make a better healer.<br>
<br>
Also, having autoattack with a sense heading attached helps keep that skill maxed. Another good idea for fighter types is to attach sense heading to taunt, which cycles a little faster than kick/bash, so you can roughly see when you should have pushed it.<br>
<br>
The where key.<br>
<br>
/doabilty 1 (sense heading)<br>
/loc<br>
<br>
This is my travelling essential for ALL characters. It's how I navigate. And it helps me learn to use both to get where I am going.<br>
<br>
Corpse key<br>
<br>
/corpse<br>
<br>
Easily edited to be<br>
/corpse name<br>
<br>
So you can drag your corpse or someone else's to safety.<br>
<br>
Run key<br>
<br>
Lately, I've been grouped with idiots. I've been running away from them when my health is low enough. They complained they missed the &quot;run&quot; in all the battlespam- which I understood, but wasn't inclined to type more while running.<br>
<br>
/g I am running for the zone like a scared little girl.<br>
/g RUN DWARF RUN<br>
/g I highly reccomend that y'all come too.<br>
/g No more heals, because I am out of here!<br>
/g RUN RUN RUN!!<br>
<br>
This of course in areas where there is more distance between party and zone line should be followed with the Train key. And at later levels, should be replaced with an Evac key:<br>
<br>
