1 key to hit.  Fish 5 times; hit key again in 1 minute.  Can be performed while medding and/or doing other trade skills like fletching.<br>
<br>
(ability 6 is, of course, fishing)<br>
<br>
/pause 120, /doability 6<br>
/pause 120, /doability 6<br>
/pause 120, /doability 6<br>
/pause 120, /doability 6<br>
/doability 6<br>
<br>
Location/SH combo key (ability 5 is Sense Heading)<br>
<br>
/loc<br>
/doability 5<br>
<br>
Language<br>
1) I have hotkeys for the different langauges I know so I can move to the right hotkey bank and just hit a number and it'll switch to one of 13 different languages I currently know.<br>
<br>
/language 3<br>
<br>
Simple key, yet so useful.  Though sometimes its easier just to type /lan 3 at the command line.<br>
<br>
2)  Teaching.  Hot key spits out 3 lines of text to group-say for teaching a language to someone you are grouped with.  The pause is necessary to by-pass the anti-spam filter.  If you leave off the pause, your group member(s) will only see the first line.<br>
<br>
/g This is a group of words spoken in a langauge you might not<br>
/pause 10<br>
/g understand.  However, this should help you learn this language<br>
/pause 10<br>
/g Please let me know when you can understand and we will move onto another.<br>
<br>
Creative RP-ish pet commands.<br>
Lots of these, usually tailored to the character I'm playing.<br>
<br>
PTGM<br>
/pet guard me (or /pet follow)<br>
/em slaps %m on the back<br>
/say Alright, %m, you're with me.<br>
<br>
OR<br>
/pet guard me<br>
/em pets %m and scratches her behind the ears.<br>
/say I need you to protect me, %m.  Good girl.<br>
<br>
PTGH<br>
/pet guard here<br>
/say Okay, %m, stay here and wait, please.<br>
<br>
PTRPT<br>
/pet report health<br>
/say Hey, %m, you still alive, buddy?<br>
<br>
PTAT<br>
/pet attack<br>
/say I found your lunch, %m, go get %t!<br>
<br>
OR<br>
<br>
/pet attack<br>
/say Rip %t's limbs off, %m!<br>
<br>
SPELL CASTING<br>
Like the pet commands, I like to add a little RP stuff into some hotkeys.  Now, I don't hit them everytime, as the saying would get really old really fast, but every 5th use or something similar.  I normally cast with ALT-number.<br>
<br>
HEAL (starting from seated or standing, returns to meditate ... the pause-double-cast is fizzle insurance, spell seven is the heal spell of choice, the second pause is to allow enough time to finish casting before sitting)<br>
<br>
/sit off<br>
/say %t, turn away from sin and be faithful to Tunare!<br>
/pause 2, /cast 7<br>
/pause 50, /cast 7<br>
/book<br>
<br>
STRIKE (combat spell for pulling or just jeering the MoB while casting a DD, spell 1 is the DD of choice)<br>
<br>
/say May Brell burn you where you stand, %T!<br>
/cast 1<br>
<br>
OR<br>
<br>
/say Cazic Thule grows weary of your existence, %T ... die!<br>
/cast 1<br>
<br>
OR<br>
(spell 1 is lifetap line)<br>
<br>
/say You have found disfavor with Innorruuk, %t, you're life is MINE!<br>
/cast 1<br>
<br>
ROOT-MEZ (Basic MoB control hotkey, spell 4 is root/mez, cast-pause-cast is fizzle insurance)<br>
<br>
/say Halt where you stand, %T!<br>
/pause 2, /cast 4<br>
/cast 4<br>
<br>
/say %t is being MEZmerized.  Do not engage until you are fully prepared.<br>
/pause 2, /cast 4<br>
/cast 4<br>
<br>
BUFF (basic buffs like shield or a skin, etc.  spell 8 is this spell)<br>
<br>
/say May Tunare protect you in your travels, %T.<br>
/pause 2, /cast 8<br>
/cast 8<br>
<br>
OR<br>
<br>
/say May Innoruuk's hate flow through your body always, %T<br>
/pause 2, /cast 8<br>
/cast 8<br>
<br>
That's a basic rundown of the ones I typically use ... but I'm always adding others ...<br>
<br>
Mojynx<br>
(and others)<br>
