<br>
I group them by &quot;theme&quot; as well. For example, all my melee's have a fighting hotkey bank with all skills for fighting (like taunt, kick, mend, Flying Kick etc., depending on class). For my druid I have one bank for the spell book hotkeys, one bank for normal travel, one for casting etc. Swichting is easy by pressing SHIFT plus the number. E.g. SHIFT-1 is bank number one, SHIFT-2 is bank number 2 and so on.<br>
<br>
Another neat trick is going to the overlay screen, where you have 10 hotkey banks compared to the 6 in &quot;normal&quot; view. Now I fill up the bank there, giving me 10 possible hotkeys per &quot;theme&quot;. Now if I switch back to normal view, I only see 6 hotkeys, but all 10 are accessible with the number keys 1 to 0. For example: on my Druid I have in my &quot;general hotkey bank&quot; to hotkeys at spot 9 and 10. 9 is a &quot;/who all friend&quot; and 10 is &quot;/who all GUILD&quot;. So by pressing 9 it shows me all my friends who are online and pressing 0 shows all of my guild, even when I don't see the hotkey itself. I hope that makes sense :-)<br>
