<br>
I have added some roleplaying touches to my pet command hot keys to add a little color and to be sure everyone knows what me and my pet are up to.<br>
<br>
I created a fishing hotkey that throws out my line and does sense heading three times.  Very helpful when medding (did this in Crushbone and caught some very nice Boar Carp...ummm, good eating!).<br>
<br>
I have a whole bank dedicated to my inventory slots, which allows quick access without going into the Persona screen.<br>
<br>
However, I have to say that the most important key that I have setup so far is the Assist Hotkey.  With a single click or keystroke, I target the doomed MOB, sic my pet onto it, and inform the group that my pet is on its way into the fray.  I think this helps to let the group know that I have my pet under control and that I am a contributing group member as well even when sitting with my nose in my book!<br>
<br>
Along the same lines, I want to create some spellcasting Hotkeys as well, to clearly communicate what I am nuking and when.  Plus from my understanding, if you are blinded you can still cast from a hotkey if you are already targeted.  I don't know if any MOBs cast blindness spells or not, but I know it happens in PvP from what I have read on various message boards.<br>
<br>
My problem is organizing all those hotkeys.  Does the Assist key go on the Pet Commands bank or the combat bank?  Where will I use it most?  Etc.  Its all personal preference, but it will take time to figure out what I am most comfortable with.<br>
<br>
A quick note to fellow newbies, you can switch between Hotkey banks with Shift and then the number of the hotkey bank that you want.  For example, your about to die so you want to switch to your corpse recovery hotkey bank.  You hit Shift-8 and switch to the bank with Corpse, Loc, Yell,  Hide/Sneak, etc on it and then Shift-1 to switch back to your combat bank once you have looted your corpse.<br>
<br>
